response.overview: Guided by his tupuna, Zane Wedding of Ngati Kuri and Ngati Pikiao, has been a relentless defender of nga rakau and advocate against social injustices. A master arborist, he once occupied a Puriri tree for 100 days to prevent the destruction of native trees. Now, standing at the brink of destiny, balancing the pursuit of a world title with the pressing need to protect his heritage and environment. Which will prevail?
response.tagline: Balancing legacy and destiny: Zane Wedding's fight for heritage and the world.
response.title: Tu Tonu
